      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Although categorical perception is a well-established phenomenon in speech research, its existence is much harder to demonstrate in the rhythm domain. In a well-known set of experiments, skilled musicians were asked to judge the length of temporal intervals in rather simple integer ratios (Sternberg, Knoll, &c Zukofsky, 1982) . Surprisingly, they were not able to do this accurately, and boundaries between different categories turned out to be rather vague. [CITATION_1] was somewhat more successful in showing the existence of a categorical boundary in interpolations between patterns of three interonset intervals."
